==Anime soundtracks== ===Motteke! Sailor Fuku=== {{Infobox Single | | Name = Motteke! Sailor Fuku | Cover = | Artist = [[Aya Hirano]], [[Emiri KatÅ]], [[Kaori Fukuhara]], and [[Aya EndÅ]] | from Album = | B-side = | Released = May 23, 2007 | Format = [[Maxi single|Maxi]] | Recorded = | Genre = [[Single (music)|Single]] | Length = 4:18 | Label = [[Lantis (company)|Lantis]] | Writer = | Producer = | Certification = | Last single = | This single = | Next single = }} {{Nihongo|'''''Motteke! Sailor Fuku'''''|ãã£ã¦ãï¼ã»ã¼ã©ã¼ãµã|Motteke! SÄrÄfuku|Take It! Sailor Uniform}} is a [[Single (music)|single]] by [[Aya Hirano]], [[Emiri KatÅ]], [[Kaori Fukuhara]], and [[Aya EndÅ]] which was used as the opening theme to the anime ''Lucky Star''. It was released on May 23, 2007 by [[Lantis (company)|Lantis]]. Upon its release, the single reached the number two spot on the weekly [[Oricon]] charts.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2007-06-27/lucky-star-special-edition|title=Lucky Star Special Edition DVD Flies off Shelves in Akiba|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=June 27, 2007|accessdate=2007-06-27}}</ref> The opening video of the anime contains this song and a choreographed dance routine. It too gained popularity via the Internet, being frequently the subject of parody and some fans considered it to be the next ''[[List of Haruhi Suzumiya albums#Hare Hare Yukai|Hare Hare Yukai]]''; both sequences were animated by the same studio &mdash; [[Kyoto Animation]]. In 2007, "Motteke! Sailor Fuku" won the Radio Kansai Award, a subset of the [[Animation Kobe#Animation Kobe Theme Song Award|Animation Kobe Theme Song Award]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Ghibli's Takahata, Paprika, Geass Win Anime Kobe Awards |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |date=2007-09-27 |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2007-09-27/ghibli%27s-takahata-paprika-geass-win-anime-kobe-awards |accessdate=2009-04-18}}</ref> The song was used in the Japanese Wii video game ''Taiko no Tatsujin''.
;Track listing #{{Nihongo|"Take It! Sailor Uniform"|ãã£ã¦ãï¼ã»ã¼ã©ã¼ãµã|Motteke! SÄrÄfuku}} â 4:18 #{{Nihongo|"Return Them! Knee Socks"|ãããã¦ï¼ãã¼ã½ãã¯ã¹|Kaeshite! NÄ«sokkusu}} â 4:06 #{{Nihongo|"Take It! Sailor Uniform" (off vocal)|ãã£ã¦ãï¼ã»ã¼ã©ã¼ãµã|Motteke! SÄrÄfuku}} â 4:18 #{{Nihongo|"Return Them! Knee Socks" (off vocal)|ãããã¦ï¼ãã¼ã½ãã¯ã¹|Kaeshite! NÄ«sokkusu}} â 4:06{{clear}}
===Lucky Star Ending Theme Collection=== {{Infobox Album | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Albums --> | Name = Lucky Star Ending Theme Collection: One Day Karaoke Box | Type = Soundtrack | Artist = [[Aya Hirano]], [[Emiri KatÅ]], [[Kaori Fukuhara]], and [[Aya Endo]] | Cover = | Background = | Released = July 11, 2007 | Recorded = | Genre = [[Anime soundtrack]] | Length = | Label = [[Lantis (company)|Lantis]] | Producer = | Reviews = | Last album = | This album = | Next album = }} {{Nihongo|'''''Lucky Star Ending Theme Collection: One Day Karaoke Box'''''|ããâããã¨ã³ãã£ã³ã°ãã¼ãéï½ããæ¥ã®ã«ã©ãªã±ããã¯ã¹ï½|RakiâSuta Endingu TÄma ShÅ«: Aruhi no Karaoke Bokkusu}} is an album containing the first twelve ending themes of the anime ''Lucky Star'' by [[Aya Hirano]], [[Emiri KatÅ]], [[Kaori Fukuhara]], and [[Aya Endo]]. The album was released on July 11, 2007 by [[Lantis (company)|Lantis]]. The first twelve tracks are the versions played in the anime, and the last thirteen are the full-length versions; the only track that did not have a TV-size version on this album was "Go! Godman".
